HEADWORD: Lordosis
<hw>Lor*do"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ , fr. <?/ bent so as to be convex in front.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A curvature of the spine forwards, usually in the
lumbar region.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any abnormal curvature of the
bones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lords and Ladies</ent>⟦br⟧
